# =============================================================================
# EXAMPLE PRIVATE KEY — REPLACE WITH YOUR OWN, DO NOT USE AS-IS
# =============================================================================
#
# This file shows the format of the Ed25519 private key required by the
# Open Payments / Interledger SDK.  The real file must be named:
#
#   private.key          ← placed in this same directory (src/server/)
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR KEY PAIR
# ─────────────────────────
#  1. Go to  https://wallet.interledger-test.dev
#  2. Sign up / log in and create a wallet (e.g. "pandapay")
#  3. Open  Settings → Developer Keys → "Add public key"
#  4. Click "Generate key pair" — the wallet generates an Ed25519 key pair,
#     shows the public key (auto-uploaded), and lets you download the private
#     key file.
#  5. Download it — save the file as  src/server/private.key
#  6. Copy the Key ID shown on screen into your .env  (KEY_ID=...)
#
# FILE FORMAT (Ed25519, PKCS#8 DER wrapped in PEM)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The downloaded file will look exactly like this, with real base64 content:
#
-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----
MC4CAQAwBQYDK2VwBCIEIXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
-----END PRIVATE KEY-----
#
# The line starting with "MC4CAQAwBQYDK2Vw" is the PKCS#8 header for Ed25519.
# The X's represent your 32-byte private key encoded in base64 — never share it.
#
# SECURITY REMINDER
# ─────────────────
# private.key is listed in .gitignore — it will NOT be committed to git.
# Never share or commit this file.  Keep it out of logs and chat messages.
# =============================================================================
